.TH SHAPE2PS 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-shapetools" "SmartMet Tools"
.SH NAME
shape2ps \- render shapefiles and querydata contours as PostScript
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shape2ps
.I controlfile
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shape2ps
reads a control file and writes a PostScript document on standard
output. The control file is, by default, plain PostScript: every line
that does not begin with one of the
.B shape2ps
keywords is copied through verbatim, and the program emits the
necessary header automatically.
.PP
Special keywords give access to the shapefile, GSHHS, querydata and
projection facilities of the SmartMet stack. They include
.BR projection ,
.B body
(end of header / start of body),
.BR boundingbox ,
.B shape
and
.B subshape
(render an ESRI shapefile),
.B gshhs
(render a GSHHS shoreline binary),
.BR graticule ,
.B exec
and
.B qdexec
(run PostScript fragments per shape vertex or grid point),
.B project
and
.B location
(emit the projected coordinates of a point or named place),
.B querydata ,
.BR parameter ,
.BR level ,
.BR timemode ,
.B time
(select the active querydata field),
.BR smoother ,
.BR contourcommands ,
.B contourline
and
.B contourfill
(produce isoline / isoband paths) and
.BR bezier .
A typical control file therefore looks like
.PP
.RS 4
projection stereographic,25:20,55,29,59:600,\-1
.br
% PostScript helpers (procedures for moveto, colors, ...)
.br
body
.br
% PostScript body that calls shape, gshhs, querydata, ...
.RE
.PP
Often the result is post\(hyprocessed into a raster image, e.g.\&
.PP
.RS 4
shape2ps map.ctl > map.ps
.br
convert map.ps map.png
.RE
.PP
The full set of keywords and their arguments is documented in the
prose document
.IR docs/shape2ps.md
in the source distribution; see also the projection description
reference for the syntax accepted by
.BR projection .
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I controlfile
The control file to render. The PostScript output is written to
standard output.
.SH EXAMPLES
Render a control file:
.PP
.RS 4
shape2ps map.ctl > map.ps
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shape2svg (1),
.BR shape2xml (1),
.BR shapefilter (1),
.BR shapeproject (1),
.BR gshhs2shape (1)
